“Cinematic 3D hand-painted travel poster titled ‘THE ROSE OF UNITED KINGDOM’. Central composition features a majestic red English rose in full bloom glowing softly in golden sunlight, surrounded by delicate petals and a radiant Art Deco halo. Behind the rose, panoramic scenery of iconic British landmarks — Big Ben, Tower Bridge, London Eye, St Paul’s Cathedral, Windsor Castle, Edinburgh Castle, and the green hills of the Cotswolds — painted in detailed fine-art realism with gentle depth blur. Foreground includes royal guards, doves in flight, and subtle rose vines curling along the frame. Elegant tourists strolling through rose gardens, reflections on the River Thames, and warm sunset tones blending ruby, gold, jade, and ivory hues. Framed by a symmetrical golden Art Deco border with geometric patterns and national floral emblems (rose, thistle, daffodil, shamrock) at the corners. Typography: ‘UNITED KINGDOM’ in luxurious embossed gold Deco font centered at bottom; small text ‘Discover the Beauty of the United Kingdom’ beneath it in fine sans-serif lettering. Lighting cinematic HDR, painterly texture, glowing highlights, ultra-detailed brushwork, fine-art poster aesthetic, 8K render.”

Foreground with royal guards under lamplight and flying doves. Typography: ‘UNITED KINGDOM’ embossed in metallic gold along the bottom, elegant sans-serif subtitle ‘Where Night Shines with Heritage’. HDR cinematic lighting, realistic textures, reflections, painterly atmosphere, fine-art 8K rendering.”
